properties.name: Wisconsin Lake Superior Scenic Byway
properties.description: This state scenic byway follows the Lake Superior coast for 70 miles along State Trunk Highway 13 through Washburn, Bayfield, Red Cliff, Cornucopia, Herbster and Port Wing.

properties.name: Great River Road National Scenic Byway
properties.description: The Great River Road is a national scenic byway along the Mississippi River that extends from Minnesota to Louisiana. The Wisconsin route mostly follows State Trunk Highway 35 for 242 miles from Prescott at the Minnesota border to the Illinois border near Dubuque, Iowa.

properties.name: Door County Coastal Byway
properties.description: Thia state scenic byway in Door County is 66 miles long and starts near Sturgeon Bay. It follows State Trunk Highway 42 to the north along Green Bay through Fish Creek, Ephraim, Sister Bay, Ellison Bay and Gills Rock to Northport and then continues south along Lake Michigan following State Trunk Highway 57 through Bailey's Harbor and Jacksonport on the way back to Sturgeon Bay.

properties.name: Lower Wisconsin River Road
properties.description: The state scenic byway follows the Wisconsin River for 100 miles along State Trunk Highway 60 from Lodi, through Prairie du Sac and Spring Green to Prairie du Chien.
